        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 9:33PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 932 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hayneville, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mosses, Hayneville, White Hall, Gordonville, Beechwood, Strata, Hope
Hull, Snowdoun, Sprague, Sellers, Davenport, Pintlala, Naftel,
Calhoun, and Letohatchee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
